()Identity aur Account same nahi hote, ye alag concepts hai.

1️⃣ Identity:-
Definition: Identity = ek real person ya entity jo system me exist karta hai.
Iska focus who the person is aur unke attributes pe hota hai.
Example attributes:-
Name → Rahul Singh
Employee ID → 12345
Department → IT
Email → rahul@example.com
Key point: Identity ka concept human / real-world entity se linked hai.

2️⃣ Account:-
Definition: Account = ek identity ka system me representation.
Ye ek specific application ya system me login credentials aur permissions ko represent karta hai.
Example:-
AD account → username: rahul123, password: ****
SAP account → userid: RAHUL_IT, roles: Admin, User
Key point: Account ka concept system-level identity se linked hai.

()1️⃣ Accounts (User Accounts / System Accounts):-
Account = ek user ka representation kisi particular application ya system me.
Matlab agar Rahul naam ka user hai aur uske paas SAP, Salesforce, aur Email system ke credentials hain, to har ek system ke liye ek Account create hoga SailPoint me.
Structure example:-
Identity Name	Application	    Account Name	Entitlements
Rahul-------- -------SAP----------r.rahul--------Read, Write
Rahul------------Salesforce-------rahul.sf---------Admin
Rahul---------------Email--------rahul@mail-----Send, Receive

Har account ke saath entitlements / roles / permissions link hote hain.
Accounts ke through SailPoint track karta hai ki kaun sa user kis system me kya access le raha hai.
